data <- readRDS("/Users/student/Documents/MATH 421/midterm/final.rda")
data %>% names()
##  [1] "yod"      "pay_ub92" "age"      "sex"      "provider" "moa"     
##  [7] "yoa"      "mod"      "admtype"  "asource"  "preopday" "los"     
## [13] "service"  "dispub92" "payer"    "trandb"   "tot"      "b_wt"    
## [19] "pt_state" "campus"   "er_fee"   "er_chrg"  "er_mode"  "race"
#Keep er_fee but remove er_chrg. They are probably related.
data <- data[,-22]

#Turn them into numeric
data$trandb <- as.numeric(data$trandb)
data$b_wt <- as.numeric(data$b_wt)
data$er_fee <- as.numeric(data$er_fee)


#Turn categorical values into factors
data <- data %>% mutate_if(is.character, as.factor)

#inadequate information about pt_state, does not tell which state it is; too many missing values in b_wt, it is not that important anyways.
data <- data %>% select(-pt_state, -b_wt)



#further remove empty and 9 from sex and other variables
data <- data[data$sex==1 | data$sex==2,]
data <- data[data$admtype!="",]
data <- data[data$asource!="",]
data <- data[data$service!="",]
data <- data[data$service!="00",]
data <- data[data$er_mode!="",]
data <- data[data$race!="",]


#labels for payer information
labels=c("Medicare", "Medicaid", "Worker's Compensation", "Blue Cross", "Commercial insurance",
                          "Self pay", "Other", "Champus", "United Healthcare", "Coordinated Health Partners Inc", 
                          "RIte Care", "Neighborhood Health Plan of RI", "Insurance error", "Missing", "Unknown")


data$payer <- mapvalues(data$payer, levels(data$payer), labels)

#labels for service information
labels = c("Pediatrics", "Medicine", "Cardiology", "Psychiatry", "Surgery", "Ophthalmology", "ENT", "Oral Surgery", "Orthopedics", "Urology", "Gynecology",
           "Abortion", "OB  Not Delivered", "OB  Delivered", "Newborn", "Rehabilitation")

data$service <- mapvalues(data$service, levels(factor(data$service)), labels)
data$sex <- mapvalues(data$sex, levels(factor(data$sex)), c("Male", "Female"))

#labels for admission type
labels <- c("Emergency", "Urgent", "Electric", "Newborn", "Information Not Available")
data$admtype <- mapvalues(data$admtype, levels(factor(data$admtype)), labels)


# saveRDS(data, "/Users/student/Documents/MATH 421/midterm/final1.rda")
detach("package:plyr", unload = TRUE)
graph1 <- data %>% group_by(age, sex)  %>% summarize(average = mean(trandb))  %>% ggplot(aes(age,average, col=sex)) + 
geom_line() + labs(title = "Average Room & Board Charge VS AGE")
print(graph1)

graph2 <- data %>% group_by(age, sex)  %>% summarize(average = mean(tot))  %>% ggplot(aes(age,average, col=sex)) + 
geom_line() + labs(title = "Average total Charge VS AGE")

print(graph2)

graph3 <- data %>% group_by(age, sex, service) %>% summarize(average = mean(tot)) %>% ggplot(aes(age, average, col = sex)) +geom_line() + facet_wrap(.~service)
## Warning: namespace 'plyr' is not available and has been replaced
## by .GlobalEnv when processing object ''
print(graph3)

graph4 <- data %>% group_by(age, payer, moa)  %>% summarize(average = mean(tot))  %>% ggplot(aes(age,average, col=payer, size = average)) + 
geom_point() + labs(title = "Average Room & Board Charge VS AGE", subtitle="Different Payer Methods in month = {closest_state}") + transition_states(moa,
                    transition_length = 2,
                    state_length = 1)

graph5 <- data %>% ggplot(aes(payer, fill = payer)) +geom_bar() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=45, hjust=1)) + labs(title= "Counts by Payers")
print(graph5)

graph6 <- data %>% ggplot(aes(payer, tot, fill = payer)) + geom_histogram(stat="identity") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=45, hjust=1)) + labs(title= "Amount Paid by Payers")
## Warning: Ignoring unknown parameters: binwidth, bins, pad
print(graph6)

## Warning: Ignoring unknown parameters: binwidth, bins, pad
print(graph7)

graph8 <- data %>% group_by(sex, service, moa) %>% summarize(average = mean(tot)) %>% ggplot(aes(service, average, fill = sex)) + geom_histogram(stat='identity') + transition_states(moa, transition_length = 1, state_length=1) + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) + labs(title = "Average Total Charge by Month", subtitle = "Month = {closest_state}")
## Warning: Ignoring unknown parameters: binwidth, bins, pad
graph9 <- data %>% ggplot(aes(service, fill=service)) + geom_bar() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=45, hjust=1)) + transition_states(moa, transition_length=1, state_length=1.5) +labs(title = "Service Counts by Month", subtitle = "Month = {closest_state}")


graph10 <- data %>% group_by(sex, admtype, moa) %>% summarize(average = mean(tot)) %>% ggplot(aes(admtype, average, size = average, col=sex)) + geom_point() +transition_states(moa, transition_length = 2, state_length=1) + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) + labs(title = "Average Total Charge by Admission Type", subtitle = "Month = {closest_state}")
